2.4.2 Equal Error Rate
The equal error rate (EER) is also a commonly used performance metric, especially when it is challenging to find an operating point between the FAR and FRR. The EER indicates the instance of FAR and FRR intersecting. Similar to the FAR and FRR, a lower EER value is preferred. As shown in Figure 3(a), a threshold closer to 0 favors convenience (low FRR) but is less secure (high FAR), while a threshold closer to 1 favors security (low FAR) but is less convenient (high FRR). The EER balances these two points.
